HEADWORD: Asyndeton
<hw>A*syn"de*ton</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ unconnected; <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ bound together, fr.
<?/; <?/ with + <?/ to bind.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure
which omits the connective; <as>as, <ex>I came, I saw, I
conquered</ex></as>. It stands opposed to
<contr>polysyndeton</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

